{% block content %}
    <style>
        .code {
            padding: .75rem 1rem;
            background: #f1f5fd;
            border-radius: 0.25rem;
        }
        .code.span {
            padding: .25rem .5rem;
        }
    </style>
    <div>
        <h2>Protection to prevent DDoS attacks enabled!</h2>
        <p>Rate Limit define a maximum number of request a user (or bot) can make to your website.</p>
    </div>
    <hr>
    <div>
        <h2>How to set up</h2>
        <p>By default the maximum value is set to 4000 per Ip and per minute.</p>
        <p>You can change this value by creating your own config file in <code class="code span">/config/rate-limit.php</code>:</p>
        <pre class="code">
    return [
        'maxRequestsPerIpPerMinute' => 256,
    ];</pre>
    </div>
{% endblock %}